HEADWORD: Cynicism
<hw>Cyn"i*cism</hw> <pr>(s⟦icr⟧n"⟦icr⟧*s⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The doctrine of the Cynics; the quality of being cynical; the
mental state, opinions, or conduct, of a cynic; morose and contemptuous
views and opinions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

